regions.title: Antelope conflict beneath elephant
regions.description: This region contains the two antelopes engaged in a physical contest, locked horns, representing the primary conflict in the image. The cells are contiguous, forming a single region.

summary: All marked cells clearly correspond to the region where two antelopes are engaged in a conflict below the elephant, and there are no disconnected or low-confidence cells to remove. The primary conflict is accurately localized.
